                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d681">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.00111 Ship Travel/6b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to President
                            <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-06T11:10:00-05:00"
                            >October 6, 1935—11:10 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your proclamation,<note n="15" xml:id="d681fn15">No. 2142; Department of State,
                            <hi rend="italic">Press Releases</hi>, October 5, 1935, p. 256; 49 Stat.
                        3476.</note> carrying out Section 6 of the Neutrality Act,<note n="16"
                        xml:id="d681fn16">Approved August 31, 1935; 49 Stat. 1084.</note> dated
                    October 5 is being given to the press as having been issued concurrently with
                    your arms embargo proclamation.<note n="17" xml:id="d681fn17">No. 2141;
                        Department of State, <hi rend="italic">Press Releases</hi>, October 5, 1935,
                        p. 251; 49 Stat. 3474.</note> The arms embargo proclamation and your
                        statement<note n="18" xml:id="d681fn18">Department of State, <hi
                            rend="italic">Press Releases</hi>, October 5, 1935, p. 255.</note> were
                    published in this morning’s newspapers but due to the midnight hour of release
                    Section 6 proclamation not being then quite ready was not printed this morning
                    but will be in the press Monday morning.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
